CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 19, 1963, pg. 13, reads: "Alpha Graduate Chapter Officers - Above are the officers who will direct the destiny of Alpha Omicron Lambda Chapter of Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity for 1963. They were installed in office during the chapter's regular monthly meeting at the Roosevelt Hotel last week.  Left to right, seated: Wilbur C. Douglas Jr., financial secretary, the Rev. LeRoy Patrick, chaplain; Paul Williams, president; Frank E. Bolden, vice president, and John Cundieff, corresponding secretary.  Standing: Atty. Eric Springer, who stood in for the absent William Fisher, editor of the Sphinx; Henry D. McCullough, treasurer; William Dorsey, sergeant-at-arms, and Atty. Wilbur C. Douglas Sr., who swore in officers. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of Alpha Phi Alpha fraternity, seated from left: Wilbur C. Douglass Jr., Rev. LeRoy Patrick, Paul Williams, Frank E. Bolden, John Cundieff; standing: Eric Springer, Henry D. McCullough, William Dorsey, and Wilbur Douglass Sr., at Roosevelt Hotel
